Round 1:
[Patient] "How much water should I be drinking every day?"
[Healthcare Educator] "For heart failure, aim for about 8 cups of water daily."

Round 2:
[Patient] "Can I drink other fluids besides water?"
[Healthcare Educator] "Yes, but limit sugary drinks and alcohol. Stick to water, herbal tea, or low-sugar options."

Round 3:
[Patient] "Should I be monitoring my fluid intake?"
[Healthcare Educator] "Yes, keep track of how much you drink in a day to help manage heart failure."

Round 4:
[Patient] "What about caffeine? Can I still have coffee?"
[Healthcare Educator] "Limit caffeine intake to help avoid fluid retention. Try decaf or herbal teas instead."

Round 5:
[Patient] "Any tips for staying hydrated throughout the day?"
[Healthcare Educator] "Carry a water bottle with you, set reminders to drink, and sip water steadily."